y because it is generated continuously, cannot be controlled consciously, and reveals what conventional surveillance cannot access. Protecting neural data is not just a security problem. It is a human rights imperative.\"","position":{"start":{"line":96,"column":4,"offset":4920},"end":{"line":96,"column":437,"offset":5353}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":96,"column":3,"offset":4919},"end":{"line":96,"column":438,"offset":5354}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":96,"column":3,"offset":4919},"end":{"line":96,"column":438,"offset":5354}}},{"type":"text","value":"\n"}],"position":{"start":{"line":96,"column":1,"offset":4917},"end":{"line":96,"column":438,"offset":5354}}},"children":["\n",["$","p","p-0",{"className":"scroll-highlight-section mb-6 leading-[1.9] text-lg text-zinc-300 font-light tracking-wide","data-section":"true","node":"$3b:props:children:3:props:children:1:props:node:children:1","children":["$","em","em-0",{"children":"\"Neural security forces a fundamental rethink of what we mean by endpoint security. At CyberNeurix, we see neural data as the most sensitive class of information that will exist in the digital ecosystem — precisely because it is generated continuously, cannot be controlled consciously, and reveals what conventional surveillance cannot access. Protecting neural data is not just a security problem. It is a human rights imperative.\""}]}],"\n"]}]]}],"\n",["$","h2","h2-0",{"className":"scroll-highlight-section text-3xl md:text-4xl font-bold text-white mt-8 mb-6 pb-3 border-b border-purple-900/30","data-section":"true","node":{"type":"element","tagName":"h2","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Conclusion","position":{"start":{"line":98,"column":4,"offset":5359},"end":{"line":98,"column":14,"offset":5369}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":98,"column":1,"offset":5356},"end":{"line":98,"column":14,"offset":5369}}},"children":"Conclusion"}],"\n",["$","p","p-0",{"className":"scroll-highlight-section mb-6 leading-[1.9] text-lg text-zinc-300 font-light tracking-wide","data-section":"true","node":{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Neural security brain-computer interface cybersecurity is not a future problem. Consumer BCIs are shipping now. Clinical trials are enrolling patients today. The data is being generated, transmitted, and stored — largely without adequate security controls.","position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":1,"offset":5370},"end":{"line":99,"column":257,"offset":5626}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":99,"column":1,"offset":5370},"end":{"line":99,"column":257,"offset":5626}}},"children":"Neural security brain-computer interface cybersecurity is not a future problem. Consumer BCIs are shipping now. Clinical trials are enrolling patients today. The data is being generated, transmitted, and stored — largely without adequate security controls."}],"\n","$L3d","\n","$L3e","\n","$L3f","\n","$L40","\n","$L41","\n","$L42","\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n\n","$L43","\n","$L44"]}]
3d:["$","p","p-1",{"className":"scroll-highlight-section mb-6 leading-[1.9] text-lg text-zinc-300 font-light tracking-wide","data-section":"true","node":{"type":"element","tagName":"p","properties":{},"children":[{"type":"text","value":"The security community must engage with neural security now, before deployment scale makes retrofitting security impossible. The lessons of IoT security — where billions of insecure devices were deployed before the industry took security seriously — must not be repeated when the device is implanted in a human skull.","position":{"start":{"line":101,"column":1,"offset":5628},"end":{"line":101,"column":318,"offset":5945}}}],"position":{"start":{"line":101,"column":1,"offset":5628},"end":{"line":101,"column":318,"offset":5945}}},"children":"The security community must engage with neural security now, before deployment scale makes retrofitting security impossible. The lessons of IoT security — where billions of insecure devices were deployed before the industry took security seriously — must not be repeated when the device is implanted in a human skull."}]
